<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c7856a5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s3032"><num value="3032">§ 3032.</num><heading> Service credit as deck officer or junior engineer for promotion purposes</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For purposes of promotion, there shall be counted in addition to active commissioned service, service as deck officer or junior engineer.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6c7856a6-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/372/tII/s232">Pub. L. 107–372, title II, § 232</ref>, <date date="2002-12-19">Dec. 19, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/3088">116 Stat. 3088</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6c7856a7-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id6c7856a8-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id6c7856a9-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Provisions similar to this section are contained in <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s854a">section 854a of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
